{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016JKWgxmPDDp8LrDvQKCqgp","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{"category":{"name":"Ideas"},"html_url":"https://github.com/githubnext/gh-aw-trial-FSarpStats-claude/discussions/2","number":2,"title":"Daily Test Coverage Improver - Research and Plan","created_at":"2025-10-17T13:02:15Z","body":"## Repository Summary\n\n**FSharp.Stats** is a comprehensive F# library for statistical testing, linear algebra, machine learning, fitting, and signal processing. It's a mature project with substantial functionality including:\n\n- Descriptive statistics\n- Fitting algorithms (linear, nonlinear, spline regression)\n- Interpolation methods\n- Signal processing (wavelet transforms, filtering, peak detection)\n- Linear algebra operations\n- Machine learning (PCA, clustering)\n- Statistical testing (t-tests, ANOVA, H-tests, post hoc tests, etc.)\n- Optimization algorithms\n\n## Current Test Coverage State\n\n### Testing Infrastructure\n\n- **Test Framework**: Expecto (F# test framework)\n- **Coverage Tool**: AltCover\n- **Test Project**: `tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj`\n- **Build Commands**: \n  - `./build.sh runtests` - build and run tests (Linux)\n  - `./build.cmd runtestswithcodecov` - build, run tests, and generate coverage report (Windows)\n- **Coverage Report Location**: `codeCov.xml` (Cobertura format)\n\n### Existing Test Files\n\nThe project has a good foundation of test files that mirror the source structure:\n\n- **31 test files** covering major modules\n- Tests are organized in the `tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/` directory\n- Each test file typically corresponds to a source module (e.g., `Vector.fs`, `Matrix.fs`, `Testing.fs`)\n- Tests use the Expecto framework with clear test case organization\n\n### Test Organization Pattern\n\n```fsharp\nmodule TestingTests\nopen Expecto\nopen FSharp.Stats.Testing\n\n[\u003cTests\u003e]\nlet testSuiteName =\n    testList \"Module.Functionality\" [\n        testCase \"specific_test\" \u003c| fun () -\u003e\n            // Test implementation\n            Expect.equal actual expected \"Description\"\n    ]\n```\n\n## Test Coverage Improvement Plan\n\n### Strategy\n\n1. **Generate baseline coverage report** to identify gaps\n2. **Prioritize testing areas** with low coverage, focusing on:\n   - Core mathematical operations (statistical accuracy is critical)\n   - Edge cases and boundary conditions\n   - Error handling paths\n   - Complex algorithms (signal processing, optimization, ML)\n3. **Add meaningful tests** that verify correctness, not just increase coverage numbers\n4. **Focus on untested modules** or functions with no existing tests\n\n### Commands to Run Tests and Generate Coverage\n\n**On Linux (this environment):**\n```bash\n# Restore tools\ndotnet tool restore\n\n# Build the solution\ndotnet build FSharp.Stats.sln --configuration Release\n\n# Run tests with coverage\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj \\\n  --configuration Release \\\n  --no-build \\\n  /p:AltCover=true \\\n  /p:AltCoverCobertura=codeCov.xml \\\n  /p:AltCoverForce=true\n\n# View summary (if reportgenerator is available)\ndotnet reportgenerator \\\n  -reports:codeCov.xml \\\n  -targetdir:coveragereport \\\n  -reporttypes:Html\n```\n\n**Or using the build script:**\n```bash\nchmod u+x build.sh\n./build.sh runtestswithcodecov\n```\n\n### Areas for Focus\n\nBased on the extensive source tree, potential high-value testing areas include:\n\n1. **Signal Processing**: Complex algorithms in `Signal/` directory\n   - Wavelet transforms\n   - FFT operations\n   - Peak detection\n   - Filtering algorithms\n\n2. **Statistical Tests**: Already has tests, but edge cases may need coverage\n   - Boundary conditions (empty data, single element)\n   - Numerical stability tests\n   - Tie handling in rank-based tests\n\n3. **Linear Algebra**: Core operations in `Algebra/` directory\n   - Matrix decompositions (SVD, EVD)\n   - Edge cases (singular matrices, zero matrices)\n\n4. **Distributions**: Probability distributions in `Distributions/`\n   - Parameter validation\n   - Edge cases for distribution functions\n   - Numerical accuracy at distribution tails\n\n5. **Optimization**: Algorithms in `Optimization/`\n   - Convergence conditions\n   - Failure cases\n   - Boundary conditions\n\n6. **ML Algorithms**: Machine learning in `ML/`\n   - Clustering algorithms\n   - Imputation methods\n   - Distance metrics\n\n### Test Organization Guidelines\n\n- New test files should follow the pattern: `ModuleName.fs` in tests directory\n- Use Expecto's `testList` and `testCase` for organization\n- Include comments explaining the expected behavior, especially for edge cases\n- Use `TestExtensions.fs` for custom assertions and accuracy helpers\n- For numerical tests, use appropriate accuracy levels (`Accuracy.high`, `Accuracy.low`, etc.)\n\n### Opportunities for Significant Coverage Increases\n\n1. **Property-based testing**: Could add FsCheck for testing mathematical properties\n2. **Benchmark validation**: Compare results against known R/Python implementations\n3. **Integration tests**: Test combinations of functions that form common workflows\n4. **Documentation examples**: Convert documentation examples into executable tests\n\n## Questions for Maintainers\n\n1. **Coverage goals**: Is there a target coverage percentage for the project?\n2. **CI/CD integration**: Should coverage reports be uploaded to Codecov automatically in this fork?\n3. **Test data**: Are there preferred sources for test data (e.g., standard datasets, R package results)?\n4. **Critical areas**: Are there specific modules or functions that are particularly important to test thoroughly?\n5. **Known issues**: Are there any known bugs or edge cases that need test coverage?\n\n## Next Steps\n\nOnce this plan is approved, I will:\n\n1. Generate an initial coverage report to identify specific gaps\n2. Select high-value areas with low coverage\n3. Add meaningful tests focusing on correctness and edge cases\n4. Create pull requests with test improvements, including before/after coverage metrics\n5. Document any potential bugs discovered during testing\n\n---\n\n**Note**: This is an automated workflow agent. Please review and provide feedback on this plan.\n\n\n\u003e AI generated by [Daily Test Coverage Improver](https://github.com/githubnext/gh-aw-trial-FSarpStats-claude/actions/runs/18593298544)"}"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c6e358e4-5f14-41c5-b878-b3b668084367","uuid":"9c8bbb88-93f6-460e-a643-1686f6810741"}
