 properly. This is the initial setup that will enable automated test coverage improvements.\n\n## Changes Made\n\nAdded `.github/actions/daily-test-improver/coverage-steps/action.yml` which provides a reusable GitHub Action that:\n\n1. **Restores dotnet tools** - Ensures AltCover and other build tools are available\n2. **Builds the solution** - Compiles FSharp.Stats in Release configuration\n3. **Runs tests with coverage** - Executes tests using AltCover to collect coverage data\n4. **Generates coverage report** - Creates `codeCov.xml` in Cobertura format\n5. **Uploads artifacts** - Makes coverage report and logs available for download\n\n## Technical Details\n\n### Coverage Configuration\n\nThe action uses AltCover (already configured in the test project) with these parameters:\n- `AltCover=true` - Enables coverage instrumentation\n- `AltCoverCobertura=../../codeCov.xml` - Outputs Cobertura XML format to repo root\n- `AltCoverForce=true` - Forces coverage generation even if previously run\n\n### Output Files\n\n- **codeCov.xml** - Cobertura format coverage report (placed in repository root)\n- **coverage-steps.log** - Detailed log of all build and test steps for debugging\n\n### Logging\n\nEach step appends its output to `coverage-steps.log` with clear section headers, making it easy to diagnose any issues that occur during the workflow.\n\n## Testing Recommendation\n\nPlease review this configuration carefully to ensure:\n\n1. The build and test commands match your project's needs\n2. The coverage report location is appropriate\n3. The logging approach works for your debugging workflow\n4. Any project-specific requirements are addressed\n\nThe next step after this PR is merged will be to manually test these steps to verify they work correctly in the CI environment.\n\n## Next Steps\n\nAfter merge, the Daily Test Coverage Improver will:\n1. Run these steps to generate coverage reports\n2. Analyze the coverage data to identify gaps\n3. Add meaningful tests to improv